# Git workflow (ECC-inspired)

## Commit messages

```
<type>: <description>

<optional body>
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `perf`, `ci`

Use imperative mood in the subject line (“Add…”, “Fix…”).

## Pull requests

1. Consider **full branch history**, not only the last commit.
2. Use `git diff <base-branch>...HEAD` (three-dot) for the **merge-base range** when summarizing what the PR contains.
3. PR description: **what** changed, **why**, and a **test plan** (commands run, manual checks if any).
4. Push new branches with upstream: `git push -u origin <branch>` when appropriate.

For planning / TDD / review **before** Git, see **`ecc-development-pipeline.mdc`**.
